Mission: M012 - Double Three-Layer Measurement Spec
Epic: E002 - LLM Prompt, Parser, and Validator
Story: S001 - System Prompt Rewrite

## What
Rewrite MEASUREMENT_SPEC_SYSTEM_PROMPT to teach the LLM the Double Three-Layer Framework through 5 structured steps.

## Acceptance Criteria
- System prompt names the framework: 'Double Three-Layer Framework'
- Step 1: Discover Product Entities — identify 3-7 core objects with unique IDs and distinct lifecycles
- Step 1 requires exactly one heartbeat entity
- Step 1 requires entity_id matching /^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$/
- Step 2: Define Activities — past-tense lifecycle markers per entity (created, shared, deleted)
- Step 2 includes the quality test: 'Does this prove or unlock user value?'
- Step 2 explicitly excludes UI-level interactions (clicked_button, viewed_page)
- Step 3: Design Properties — catalog at entity level, activities declare properties_supported
- Step 3 explains property types: id, string, number, boolean, array, calculated, experimental, temporary
- Step 3 instructs: 'Support as many properties as possible within all activities'
- Step 4: Compose Customer Journey — single Customer entity with derived activities
- Step 4 requires derivation_rule on each customer activity with examples
- Step 4 shows derivation example: 'Board shared (first time) OR Asset created (30+ times)'
- Step 5: Define Interaction Layer — single Interaction entity with element_clicked, element_submitted
- Step 5 lists contextual properties: element_type, element_text, element_position, element_target, element_container
- Includes Miro reference example with 5 product entities and their activities
- Includes output JSON schema matching the new MeasurementSpec type from E001
- Instructs LLM to return ONLY valid JSON, no commentary
- System prompt test verifies all key sections exist

## Files to Modify
- packages/mcp-server/src/analysis/outputs/measurement-spec.ts
- packages/mcp-server/src/analysis/__tests__/outputs/measurement-spec.test.ts

## Context
Current prompt is 154 lines. New one will be ~200-250 lines. The prompt is the most important piece — it teaches the LLM how to think about tracking design. Temperature stays at 0.2. maxTokens may need to increase for richer output.

## Implementation Plan

### Summary
Rewrite the `MEASUREMENT_SPEC_SYSTEM_PROMPT` constant in `measurement-spec.ts` to teach the LLM the Double Three-Layer Framework through a 5-step structured process. The new prompt replaces the current flat entity/event model with a perspective-grouped, entity-centric structure: Product (3-7 entities with past-tense activities), Customer (single entity with derivation rules), and Interaction (single entity with generic element tracking). Includes a full Miro reference example and a JSON output schema matching the new MeasurementSpec type from E001. Tests are updated to verify all key sections exist.

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] AC1: `MEASUREMENT_SPEC_SYSTEM_PROMPT` contains the string "Double Three-Layer Framework"
- [ ] AC2: Prompt contains "Step 1" section with "Discover Product Entities", "3-7", "heartbeat", and entity ID regex `/^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$/`
- [ ] AC3: Prompt contains "Step 2" section with "Define Activities", "past-tense", quality test "Does this prove or unlock user value?", and exclusion of "clicked_button" / "viewed_page"
